 choice.  There are changes coming to them all in the near future so read up on them.  Vallon and Tallon are more "organized", and the team concept is fun.  Rallos is more chaotic and you will lose one item when you die.  Sullon will also be chaotic, but it's gonna be brand new so there won't be any twinking to start.<br><br>3)Sneak and Hide work against a foe as long as he can't see invis.  It tends to work best on melee classes (who don't have see invis).  It works best for sneak attacks and desperate retreats.<br><br>In general, rogues can thrive in a pvp environment if you know what you're doing.  Learn and work on poisons, stock up on magic resist items, and make friends with a healer/caster.<br><br>Morvran McGuinness, Barbarian Rogue<br>Shanks, Vallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/01 8:29:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=365.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Creating rogue on PvP server.. where do i start..</span><hr size=1> Yes, get a guild.<br><br> <p><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/bscreamspvp"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/sig/joyous.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=365.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=365.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.sho